<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 3:50PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Buchanan and
northwestern McDowell Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 350 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Grundy, moving north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Grundy, Bradshaw, Iaeger, Stacy, Panther, Hurley, Avondale, Roseann
and Vansant.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
